{
  "title": "Groove Bank",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Rhythm templates for the",
        "chord you HOLD. You own",
        "the pitches; Groove Bank",
        "owns the timing.",
        "",
        "Hold a chord and the",
        "groove retriggers it on",
        "the beat, through the",
        "synth in the same slot.",
        "Change chord mid-pattern",
        "and the next hit follows."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Setup",
      "lines": [
        "In a chain slot:",
        " - Sound gen: any synth",
        "   (pad, bass, keys).",
        " - MIDI FX: Groove Bank.",
        "",
        "Feed it a chord:",
        " - a USB MIDI keyboard, or",
        " - Move's pads: set the",
        "   slot Receive to All,",
        "   the track MIDI Out On,",
        "   and mute that track.",
        "",
        "You hear the CHAIN synth,",
        "not Move's own track.",
        "It plays when the",
        "transport is running."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Controls",
      "lines": [
        "jog: grooves in genre",
        "K1: variant (flavor,",
        "    shown as [+] in title)",
        "K2: strum",
        "K3: gate",
        "K4: accent",
        "K5: latch (CW on/CCW off)",
        "K7: swing",
        "K8: switch genre",
        "Click/Back: exit"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Feel knobs",
      "lines": [
        "Three knobs shape HOW",
        "each hit sounds:",
        "",
        "Strum (K2): spread the",
        " chord's notes in time",
        " (tight <-> strummed,",
        " up CW / down CCW).",
        "Gate (K3): note length",
        " (staccato <-> legato).",
        "Accent (K4): loudness",
        " spread (flat <-> punchy)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Latch",
      "lines": [
        "Latch (K5) makes a held",
        "chord STICK after you let",
        "go - the groove keeps",
        "playing hands-free.",
        "",
        "Tap a new chord to swap.",
        "Turn latch off to release.",
        "",
        "Great for comping while",
        "you solo over the top."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Grid marks",
      "lines": [
        "The row is pure rhythm:",
        "",
        " x  hit     A  accent",
        " g  ghost (soft)",
        " -  tie/sustain prev hit",
        " .  rest",
        "",
        "'A---' = one accented",
        "note held four steps.",
        "Gate (K3) sets how long",
        "the un-tied hits ring."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Your Own",
      "lines": [
        "Grooves are plain .groove",
        "text files. Drop yours in:",
        " UserData/schwung/",
        "  groovebank/patterns/",
        "",
        "One 'hit:' row + optional",
        "'alt:' flavor rows (K1",
        "morphs them). See",
        "_HOWTO.txt there for the",
        "format."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Recording",
      "lines": [
        "Record the Schwung way:",
        "Shift+Sample (Quantized",
        "Sampler) resamples the",
        "chain's audio to a WAV",
        "in Samples/Schwung/."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
